devdoc.details: A simple digital vending machine contract that allows the owner to manage items and users to purchase them. The DigitalVendingMachine smart contract is a straightforward implementation of a vending machine on the Ethereum blockchain. It allows the contract owner to manage a list of items available for purchase and enables users to buy these items by sending Ether.

addItem(string,uint256,uint256).details: Add a new item to the vending machine.

params.name: The name of the item.
params.price: The price of the item in wei.
params.quantity: The initial stock quantity of the item.

params.index: The index of the item in the array.

returns.name: The name of the item.
returns.price: The price of the item in wei.
returns.quantity: The available quantity of the item.

getItemCount().details: Get the total number of items in the vending machine.

purchaseItem(uint256,uint256).details: Purchase an item from the vending machine.

params.id: The ID of the item to purchase.
params.quantity: The number of items to purchase.

removeItem(uint256).details: Remove an item from the vending machine by its ID.

params.id: The ID of the item to remove.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfer contract ownership to a new address.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

withdrawFunds().details: Withdraw all Ether from the contract to the owner's address.
